#UMDxIBM #cybersecurity Different types of organizations need different types of security solutions - no standard. Empirical-based approach.

#UMDxIBM #Cybersecurity  
What we need from analytics: What’s the problem? How do we structure the solution? What is the value of the work?

#UMDxIBM #Cybersecurity Joe Kielman #DHS: 
How do we decide where to put limited resources? If not predict, prevent-have a prospective view
#UMDxIBM #Cybersecurity - In case you didn’t know: “Honey pots” are computers dedicated to being attacked - Michel Cukier
#UMDxIBM - Prof Michel Cukier talks now about his journey towards rigorous #cybersecurity experiments
#UMDxIBM is not even halfway done, but “I want to be a #cybersecurity ranger!” (Think #BreakfastClub) - such interesting stuff! @SmithSchool
#UMDxIBM #Cybersecurity - Greg Porpora - a cyber attack would have a much greater impact on the U.S. than a missile. http://t.co/xVhO1TANIz

#UMDxIBM #Cybersecurity Challenges
-high volume data streams
-threats emerging at high rate
-evasive threats
-high cost to prevention
#UMDxIBM - Greg Porpora: You need adaptive defense - machine learning is the future of #cybersecurity @SmithSchool
#UMDxIBM #Cybersecurity Analytics Workshop - Next up Greg Porpora, Chief Engineer, IBM Federal on applying machine learning to cyber defense
#UMDxIBM #Cybersecurity - Prof Larry Gordon: Firms should generally invest <37% of expected loss - #GordonLoebModel @SmithSchool
@SmithSchool Prof Larry Gordon: #cybersecurity is a cost savings project. You can't ever be 100% secure. #UMDxIBM http://t.co/rrsukcEu70
#UMDxIBM #Cybersecurity Breach - Larry Gordon: Explicit costs (detect, correct) are minor relative to implicit costs (reputation, liability)
#UMDxIBM #cybersecurity - How do you keep up with the threat? Bring together problem-owners and solution-owners. Get people in same room.
#UMDxIBM #Cybersecurity - “Building Blocks” are technology-specific challenges identified through public engagement
#UMDxIBM #Cybersecurity. “Use Cases” are sector-specific challenges identified through industry engagement
#UMDxIBM Barrios: We think the #cybersecurity initiatives are immediate and important @SmithSchool
#UMDxIBM Barrios: Collaborate with innovators to provide real-world, standards-based #cybersecurity capabilities that address business needs
